slidelink.displaytext: Myths & Taboos Associated with Physical Changes During Adolescence
Myths & Taboos Associated with Physical Changes During Adolescence
Skills to Counter Stigmas and Stereotypes Around
Help Neeta and Robert through their challenges by going through their dilemmas and responding to the questions that follow. While you respond, think about the concepts you learned in this module.

I am shorter than my friends and on the chubbier side. Some of my classmates make fun of me. They also call me names like tea pot. What could Neeta do? Based on your learning from this module, select all the options that you think will be helpful to Neeta in this situation.
I feel so hopeless, what should I do?
I feel so hopeless, what should I do?
I feel so hopeless, what should I do?

When I asked my father about the health drink, he sat down with me and helped me understand all about the changes that take place during adolescence. He assured me that I didn't need any health drinks and in fact, such products could be harmful too. Now I want to ensure none of my friends make the same mistake I was about to make. How can I help my friends? What steps do you think Robert can take to help his friends? Based on your learning from this module, select the options that you think are appropriate in this situation.
